==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*kerfan''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[kerva]], Middle Dutch [[kerven]] (Dutch [[kerven]]), Middle High German [[kerben]].  Perhaps cognate with Greek [[γράφειν]].

===Pronunciation===
